verses.roman:
ei ta' kahila tāṅra sevaka-prabhāva
āra eka kahi tāṅra dayāra svabhāva

synonyms: ei ta'-thus; kahila—explained; tāṅra—of Him; sevaka-prabhāva—the power of the servant; āra—other; eka—one; kahi—I say; tāṅra—His; dayāra—of mercy; svabhāva—characteristic.
translation: I have thus described the power of the servants of Lord Nityānanda. Now I shall describe another characteristic of His mercy.
